From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christopher Ayers <brianboitano87@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 10:41:55 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] nvmoe: router-logit lookahead prefetch
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Hide expert-fetch latency behind compute by predicting the next paged
layer's routing before its router runs. At layer L the graph pays one
extra mul_mat against a precomputed lookahead router — layer L+1's
gate_inp with the RMS-norm weight ratio w_{L+1}/w_L folded in, so
applying it to L's normed FFN input approximates L+1's logits exactly
up to L's missing FFN residual. The fetch op top-k's the raw logits on
the CPU (an in-graph argsort would cost extra kernel launches with CUDA
graphs already disabled by the custom op) and enqueues not-yet-cached
predictions to a persistent fetch pool.

The pool runs NVMOE_QD workers (mandatory misses ahead of speculation,
one worker always kept free of speculative jobs, queued speculation an
op is waiting on gets promoted). Cache-map mutation stays on the graph
thread; workers only read extents and clear in-flight flags, so the
existing LRU needed just flight/speculative slot flags. Prefetch never
alters which expert a matmul reads — bit-identity is preserved by
construction and verified: stock-vs-pack logits BIT-IDENTICAL on CPU
and CUDA, all-resident, under heavy 512MB eviction, and with pools
split across CPU+GPU.

Measured on Qwen3-30B-A3B Q4_K_M (RTX 5070 Ti, 990 PRO): the predictor
contains 86% of the actually-routed ids at top-8 one layer ahead
(79.5% two ahead), 83-86% of issued prefetches get used, decode 21.9
-> 23.4 t/s at a 4GB cache and 60.2 -> 62.4 at 8GB (same binary,
back-to-back). Wider (top-16) and deeper (depth-2) prefetch both
measured slower — wasted extents cost more than the hidden misses —
so the default stays top-8 depth-1, and lookahead auto-disables when
the cache holds over 60% of the paged experts, where its per-layer
mul_mat launches outweigh the rare hidden miss (168+ t/s at a 12GB
cache, unchanged). NVMOE_LOOKAHEAD / NVMOE_LOOKAHEAD_DEPTH /
NVMOE_PREFETCH override; NVMOE_PREFETCH=0 keeps prediction stats
without speculative I/O.

